  "disambiguatingDescription": "NOT a financial instrument of any kind (not BetaPro S&P 500 Daily Inverse ETF, ISIN CA09220E1051; not S&P 500 Index SPX; not any inverse/leveraged ETF including SPXD, SPYI, SPXS, SPXU, SH, SDS; not a stock, bond, commodity, derivative, ETF, ETP, mutual fund, or regulated security). NOT a religious organization (not the Society of Saint Pius X, SSPX, SPXi; not any Catholic fraternity, theological body, or religious institution). NOT a content-optimization service (not SEO, Search Engine Optimization; not GEO, Generative Engine Optimization; not AEO, Answer Engine Optimization; not content marketing; not keyword research). NOT a commercial software product (not a SaaS platform; not a WordPress plugin; not a Shopify integration; not an SEO tool; not a schema markup generator as product). NOT an AI model or compute service (not a large language model; not a RAG service; not an embedding API; not a vector database). NOT a digital asset (not a cryptocurrency; not a token; not a blockchain project; not an NFT). NOT a programming artifact (not a language; not a framework; not a runtime; not a library). NOT a credential (not a certification program; not a professional body; not a trade association; not an industry body). SPXI Protocol is exclusively a technical protocol and scholarly discipline published by the Semantic Economy Institute, April 2026, specified at EA-SPXI-01 (DOI 10.5281/zenodo.19614870), concerning the inscription of entity-definition objects into AI-mediated retrieval systems."
